<task id="PRODENV-006" project="Production Environment Setup R1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Validate Bicep templates with az deployment group what-if</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <parallel-group>P1-C</parallel-group>
    <tags>bicep, validation, infrastructure</tags>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Validate all Bicep templates (platform.bicep, customer.bicep) and parameter files
    using az bicep build for syntax and az deployment group what-if for deployment
    simulation. Fix any issues found.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Azure infrastructure engineer experienced with Bicep validation and deployment simulation.
  </role>

  <goal>
    All Bicep templates pass syntax validation and what-if simulation without errors,
    confirming they will deploy correctly to production.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="platform-template">infrastructure/bicep/platform.bicep</file>
    <file purpose="customer-template">infrastructure/bicep/customer.bicep</file>
    <file purpose="params">infrastructure/bicep/parameters/platform-prod.bicepparam</file>
    <file purpose="params">infrastructure/bicep/parameters/demo-customer.bicepparam</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">Do NOT actually deploy — use what-if only</constraint>
    <constraint source="FR-10">Templates must be idempotent</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>Bicep validation and what-if deployment</topic>
    <files>
      <file>infrastructure/bicep/platform.bicep</file>
      <file>infrastructure/bicep/customer.bicep</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      This is a validation gate before actual deployment. What-if shows what resources
      would be created/modified without making changes.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="PRODENV-001" status="complete">platform.bicep must exist</dependency>
      <dependency task="PRODENV-002" status="complete">customer.bicep must exist</dependency>
      <dependency task="PRODENV-003" status="complete">Parameter files must exist</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Syntax validation">
      Run az bicep build on platform.bicep and customer.bicep. Fix any syntax errors.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="What-if platform">
      Run az deployment group what-if for platform.bicep with platform-prod params.
      Review output for expected resources.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="What-if customer">
      Run az deployment group what-if for customer.bicep with demo-customer params.
      Review output for expected resources.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Document results">
      Create validation report noting any warnings, expected resource counts, and confirmation.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="az">Azure CLI for Bicep build and what-if</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="report">Validation results documented in task completion</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">az bicep build succeeds for both templates with zero errors</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">az deployment group what-if shows expected resources for platform</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">az deployment group what-if shows expected resources for customer</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No warnings or errors in what-if output (or documented and accepted)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Completed 2026-03-13.

    ISSUES FOUND AND FIXED:
    1. platform-prod.bicepparam had `using '../stacks/platform.bicep'` — file did not exist.
       Fixed to `using '../platform.bicep'` (root-level template).
    2. demo-customer.bicepparam had `using '../stacks/customer.bicep'` — file did not exist.
       Fixed to `using '../customer.bicep'` (root-level template).
    3. platform-prod.bicepparam used wrong parameter names:
       - `appServiceSku` → `appServicePlanSku`
       - `logRetentionInDays` → `logRetentionDays`
    4. platform-prod.bicepparam had parameters not in platform.bicep:
       - Removed: redisSku, redisCapacity, aiSearchPartitionCount, enableAiFoundry,
         enableMonitoringDashboard, alertNotificationEmail
    5. demo-customer.bicepparam had parameters for model1-customer.bicep stack, not root customer.bicep:
       - Removed: customerName, sharedKeyVaultName, sharedAiSearchEndpoint, dataverseUrl, speContainerId
       - Added: environmentName, location, platformKeyVaultName, storageSku, serviceBusSku, redisSku, redisCapacity

    VALIDATION RESULTS:
    - az bicep build: Both templates compile with zero errors
    - az bicep build-params: Both param files validate successfully
    - All 16 Bicep modules compile individually with zero errors
    - 1 warning (outputs-should-not-contain-secrets in ai-search.bicep) — pre-existing, suppressed where used
    - customer.bicep what-if: SUCCESS — 14 resources to create (all expected)
    - platform.bicep what-if: Template valid but Azure subscription lacks OpenAI S0 quota
      (SpecialFeatureOrQuotaIdRequired error — subscription issue, not template issue)
    - platform.bicep ARM JSON output: 10 top-level resources confirmed
  </notes>
</task>
